title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link
type="local"
href="ring-0001.xml"
addr="ring-0001"
title="Ring">Ring</fr:link>. A <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Right Module</html:dfn> over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> is an additive group <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> equipped with a function <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M\times  R\to  M]]></fr:tex> denoted <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(m,r)\mapsto  m\cdot  r]]></fr:tex> called scalar multiplication, such that
<fr:ol><fr:li>For any <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m_{1},m_{2}\in  M]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[r\in  R]]></fr:tex>, we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(m_{1}+m_{2})r=(m_{1}r)+(m_{2}r)]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>For any <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m\in  M]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[r_{1},r_{2}\in  R]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m(r_{1}+r_{2})=(mr_{1})+(mr_{2})]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>Associativity of scalar multiplication: For any <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m\in  M]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[r_{1},r_{2}\in  R]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m(r_{1}r_{2})=(mr_{1})r_{2}]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>If <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[R]]></fr:tex> is unital, then we call <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> <html:dfn
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Unital</html:dfn> when for any <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m\in  M]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m\cdot  1=m]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol></fr:p>
 
   
